- PROCEDURAL PROGRAMMING:- procedures/methods are written
    -> fixed flow
    -> tightly coupled (depends on other funcs output)
- OBJECT ORIENTED PROGRAMMING:- objects are created
    -> loosely coupled (less dependency on other factors)
    -> faster than procedural and clear structure
    -> reusability. 
